10. Etc(Permission Requests)
Smartwho's app contain sensitive information. In order to use seamless app services, you need the indicated permissions. You may terminate your use of this permission at any time.
-
The Special Days (Package name: com.smartwho.smartdday)
* android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE, android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
						* The Special Days - Lunar Support is an app that saves anniversaries and gives you reminders.
* Among the main functions, it provides the function of saving an image symbolizing anniversaries in the app and giving a notification, and to support this function, [ media file write permission (WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE) ] is required.
* If that permission does not allow, anniversary registration will be restricted.
-
Smart App Manager (Package name: com.james.SmartUninstaller)
* android.permission.QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES, android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE, android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
* Storage space permission (optional): Required when using app backup and reinstallation services. Storage space access permission is required to use the backup and reinstall function, a service of the smart app manager. Storage space access rights are optional and are not required when using services other than backup and reinstallation. Limited use only for reading and writing app installation apk files.
* App usage information permission (optional): We provide a service that recommends customized apps to customers using usage statistics.
-
Magnetic Field Meter (Package name: com.smartwho.smartmetaldetector)
* android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION, android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION, android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
* This permission is required to provide the measurement value of the magnetic field and the current location information at the same time.
* The storage space access permission is optional and can be revoked at any time. However, at this time, you may not be able to use the main app functions.
-
Sound Meter (Package name: com.smartwho.smartsoundmeter)
* android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION, android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION, android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE, android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO
* This permission is required to provide noise measurement values and current location information at the same time.
* The storage space access permission is optional and can be revoked at any time. However, at this time, you may not be able to use the main app functions.
11. Supplementary Provisions
1)
In the case of an amendment to this privacy policy, SmartWho shall announce the reason for the amendment, and the effective date of the amendment, along with the current, effective privacy policy on a service page starting from 10 days in advance of the effective date and up to one day in advance of the effective date.
However, when there are changes to significant details concerning the rights and obligations of the user, the announcement shall be made at least 30 days in advance.
2)
If the user does not explicitly express their refusal, despite SmartWho’s announcement that the user’s acceptance would be deemed as expressed unless the user clearly expresses their refusal before the effective date of the amendment, as SmartWho announces the amendment in accordance with Paragraph 1, the user will be deemed as having accepted the amendment.
3)
Despite Paragraph 2, if SmartWho needs to collect additional personal information from the user, or provide additional personal information to third parties, SmartWho shall obtain additional consent to do so directly from the user.
This privacy policy shall enter into effect on January 15, 2017.
